The Kenya medical Training Collegeâ€™s Busia campus has started offering nursing courses after the Nursing Council approved it. Head of Nursing Department Heronimo Wesonga on Tuesday said 100 students have enrolled for nursing courses. Another 91 are taking clinical medicine. He said the campus started admitting students in May this year. The second batch was admitted in September. The third admission will be in March 2018. Wesonga said the advertisement for various courses in nursing were published in dailies onTuesday. He appealed to those interested to follow the application guidelines on the website www.kmtc.ac.ke.  Wesonga said they can take their application forms to the HOD Nursing Busia Campus.